Chrysopogon plumulosus

    Authority   Hoch
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4544

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A tufted, leafy grass reaching up to 50 cm in height
   with slender, wiry culms. USES Very palatable, of high nutritive value
   and used for pasture. GROWING PERIOD Summer-growing perennial grass.
   COMMON NAMES Aucher's grass, Agarab, Teerab, Daremo, Baremho,
   Esidokomom, Esangash. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: C. aucheri var.
   quinqueplumis, C. aucheri var. pulvinatus, C. quinqueplumis, C.
   serrulatus. Aucher's grass can be found within the latitudinal range
   30°N and 10°S, at elevations between sea level and 2000 m. It is common
   on dry, gravelly, often rather alkaline soils with garss or semi-desert
   cover and is very drought resistant.

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. plumulosus Hochst.)
   Skerman P 1990 pp 298-299 [DRA, PH, TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, TEXT]
   White F 1983 pp 116 121 222
   IBPGR 1984 pp 144
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 88-89 [RAIN, TEXT DEP]

